annotationA: tRNA methyltransferase 10 homolog A; S-adenosyl-L-methionine-dependent guanine N(1)- methyltransferase that catalyzes the formation of N(1)- methylguanine at position 9 (m1G9) in tRNAs
annotationB: Probable tRNA (guanine(26)-N(2))-dimethyltransferase; Dimethylates a single guanine residue at position 26 of most tRNAs using S-adenosyl-L-methionine as donor of the methyl groups
